Defendant Errol C Collins in court with attorney Allison Marie Ritter.  Defendant Errol C Collins in custody.  Zachary A Wittchow appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court finds State has complied with victim notification.  Sentencing hearing held.  Statements made as to sentencing.  

The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 5 YEARS (CONSECUTIVE TO ANY OTHER SENTENCE), with credit for 4 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS AND 6  MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 2 YEARS AND 6 MONTHS.  The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is not eligible for the "Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program".

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 4 YEARS.
Court orders the following conditions of probation and extended supervision:    
*Serve 12 MONTHS in the House of Correction with huber release for work and childcare (REPORT DATE 6/10/16);
*No weapons;
*Maintain full time employment;
*Anger management programming;
*No contact with residence where shooting occurred (3369 N 27th St, Milwaukee, WI);
*Absolute sobriety;
*No new offenses that rise to the level of probable cause;
*Any other terms and conditions deemed appropriate by the department of corrections. 
Court orders restitution set at $0. 
Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs and surcharges.
As to all costs and surcharges, Court orders amounts to be deducted form bail on deposit, remaining balance to be returned to the person who posted it.  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor.  Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored. 

